quran[30]{c,v,t,f}:
  74,37,"To any of you that chooses to go forward (by working righteous deeds), or to remain behind (by committing sins)."
  74,38,"Every person is a pledge for what he has earned,"
  74,39,"Except those on the Right, (i.e. the pious true believers of Islâmic Monotheism)."
  75,34,"Woe to you [O man (disbeliever)]! And then (again) woe to you!"
  75,35,"Again, woe to you [O man (disbeliever)]! And then (again) woe to you!"
  75,36,"Does man think that he will be left neglected (without being punished or rewarded for the obligatory duties enjoined by his Lord Allâh on him)?"
  76,28,"It is We Who created them, and We have made them of strong built. And when We will, We can replace them with others like them with a complete replacement."
  76,29,"Verily, this (Verse of the Qur’ân) is an admonition, so whosoever wills, let him take a Path to his Lord (Allâh)."
  76,30,"But you cannot will, unless Allâh wills. Verily, Allâh is Ever All-Knowing, All-Wise."
  77,25,"Have We not made the earth a receptacle"
  77,26,"For the living and the dead?"
  77,27,"And have placed therein firm, and tall mountains, and have given you to drink sweet water?"
  78,22,"A dwelling place for the Tâghûn (those who transgress the boundary limits set by Allâh like polytheists, disbelievers in the Oneness of Allâh, hyprocrites, sinners, criminals),"
  78,23,"They will abide therein for ages."
  78,24,"Nothing cool shall they taste therein, nor any drink."
  79,16,"When his Lord called him in the sacred valley of Tûwâ,"
  79,17,"Go to Fir‘aun (Pharaoh); verily he has transgressed all bounds (in crimes, sins, polytheism, disbelief)."
  79,18,"And say to him: "
  80,13,"(It is) in Records held (greatly) in honour (Al-Lauh Al-Mahfûz),"
  80,14,"Exalted (in dignity), purified,"
  80,15,"In the hands of scribes (angels)."
  81,10,"And when the (written) pages [of deeds (good and bad) of every person] are laid open."
  81,11,"And when the heaven is stripped off and taken away from its place;"
  81,12,"And when Hell-fire is set ablaze."
  82,4,"And when the graves are turned upside down (and bring out their contents)"
  82,5,"(Then) a person will know what he has sent forward and (what he has) left behind (of good or bad deeds)."
  82,6,"O man! What has made you careless about your Lord, the Most Generous?"
  83,1,"Woe to Al-Mutaffifûn (those who give less in measure and weight)."
  83,2,"Those who, when they have to receive by measure from men, demand full measure,"
  83,3,"And when they have to give by measure or weight to (other) men, give less than due."